      "key": {
        "uuid": "4071fe59_436e3f57",
        "filename": "cipd/client/cipd/plugin/admission/host.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 364,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-06T21:56:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There are two concurrent termination paths, it is one of them.\n\nOnce the host decides to stop, it:\n1. Replies with codes.Aborted to ListAdmissions.\n2. Closes plugin\u0027s stdin.\n\n(2) can potentially win the race, which will end up in the plugin canceling ListAdmissions on its own before receiving codes.Aborted (it manifests as \u0027ctx\u0027 in dequeue here being canceled).\n\nThe termination path that uses stdin is a more general one and works for any kind of plugin. The path (1) exists because it just handles all potential edge cases (i.e. there\u0027s probably a way to get rid of it, but it will make code more complicated).",
      "parentUuid": "4ec99fc8_8e77ac17",
      "revId": "e30a53777b429556f6fdbbf90b91dd9f1120176d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
